Lloyds Bank Canada, a unit of &lt;LloydsBank International PLC>, said net profit soared to 3,053,000dlrs for the first quarter ended January 31 from 9,000 dlrs ayear earlier.    Loan loss provisions, a mandatory five-year averaging ofactual loan losses, also rose in the first quarter to 6,375,000dlrs from year-ago 113,000 dlrs, the bank said.    Lloyds Bank Canada became Canada's largest foreign banklast autumn with its 200 mln Canadian dlr acquisition ofContinental Bank of Canada. Reuter&#3;